1: James Wynn: If Bitcoin reaches a peak of $118,000-122,000, the market may see a cooling or sideways trend;
2: The founder of Farcaster confronted Vitalik in a new article, and Vitalik said that the other party should consider selling ETH;
3: The 5-fold short position of HYPE whale closed, and the loss was as high as $23.522 million in 30 days;
4: Trump urged the EU to cut tariffs, otherwise it will face more tariffs;
5: SOON released token economics, and the live-broadcast copy tool Simpfor.fun V2 was launched simultaneously;
6: The chairman of the China-Britain Trade Association called on the US government: act rationally and get out of the quagmire of tariff wars;
7: The founder of aiPool ridiculed a HYPE short position for a loss of more than $21 million;
8: Uniswap Foundation: $115 million has been allocated in 2024;
9: The stablecoin project Plasma received strategic investment from Peter Thiel's Founders Fund;
10: Virtuals The latest new project VIRGEN has a market value of over 10 million USD;
11: Ondo Finance launches on-chain securities trading platform "Ondo Global Markets";
12: Upbit will launch SOON spot trading;
13: Upbit will launch KERNEL spot trading;
14: BitMart founder Sheldon Xia was invited to attend Trump's VIP dinner;
15: A whale/institution sold 184.4 WBTC through Wintermute today;
16: NXPC briefly broke through 2.1 USDT, possibly due to a 3-fold increase in the game's reward drop rate;
17: HYPE rose above 35 USDT, with a 24-hour increase of 17.7%;
18: Justin Sun attended President Trump's dinner and delivered a speech: Thank the President for supporting the crypto industry.
